        <headline>Tornado Warning issued June 8 at 3:56PM EDT until June 8 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm capable of producing a tornado
was located over New Stanton, or 6 miles south of Jeannette, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated rotation.

IMPACT...Flying debris will be dangerous to those caught without
shelter. Mobile homes will be damaged or destroyed.
Damage to roofs, windows and vehicles will occur. Tree
damage is likely.

Locations impacted include...
Greensburg, Youngwood, New Stanton, Madison, Arona and Hunker.
</description>
        <instruction>Move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a well-built
building away from windows. If you are outdoors, in a mobile home,
or in a vehicle, move to the closest substantial shelter and protect
yourself from flying debris.

Highway overpasses are not safe shelters. If you cannot safely drive
away from the tornado, as a last resort, abandon your vehicle and
lie down in a low lying area and protect yourself from flying debris.</instruction>
